snippet.textDisplay: Hey Demi Lovato, Things have got be hard for you and you have probably ask for help from God before but, just because you dont get an answer doesnt mean Jesus is not there for you. He is just waiting for you to give up the hard things in life, the things that have got you in a different dark world apart from his world. I have been threw alot in life and have done alot of bad things and yet i still dont give up in jesus even if he may not answer me. I know he's there, he just wants what's best for all of us. We always know what would be a better choice but dont always make that better choice because we wanna do it our way. So how can God help us if we aren't letting him. Bad things happen to us either because we put our selfs in that position, because someone made a bad decision, or because God has a plan, or that someone might learn a lesson that they might have not seen before. There is always a reason for everything even when we dont know... Demi Lovato, i watch you so much when i was young and loved your old music because it was about real pain true feelings. There is a song of yours that was one of my favorites, it's called FOR THE LOVE OF A DAUGHTER. This song got me so good because i felt your pain and i loved how you sang as tho you were actually saying right to your father. I don't know for sure if that song applies to you but if it does Demi, im so sorry.... If you dont feel nobody sees your pain well that's not true... I see your pain, Jesus sees, and I'm sure there are more we do not know about...  Why that song really got to me was because my mom and dad had 6 kids including me. My dad was abusive, didn't take care of us and my mom. He went to prison for sexauly abusing me when i was a little girl. And from then things have tough. But i dont give up on Jesus because he didnt make life hard on me, people making bad choices did. And if we make bad choices we"ll make it hard on others too. I'll pray that you find true happyness Demi and that you'll feel Jesus's love you. He loves you even tho you have done wrong.

snippet.textDisplay: I just lost my brother, who was also my very best friend in this world of mine, on December 18th. I feel so completely all alone, in a crowded room. Like I can't get anyone to understand how major this is. Like, in my head, im thinking, "why is the world continuing on without him?". My sadness gets to me to a point where its uncontrollable and so dark. I can feel Demi's words when she is asking for anyone. Anyone to truly listen. Anyone to understand. Very proud of you Demi Lovato. - Your Fellow Texan

snippet.textDisplay: The pain she has gone through is tremendous. Her emotion in her voice is so strong it literally gave me chills within the first minute of this performance. People assume that “fame and fortune” brings happiness and that can only take you so far. As someone who has suffered from severe depression alone when she sang “Cause nobody is listening to me.” That just hits home for me. Just a year ago if someone would have said I would be where I am today I would have never believed it at all. Truly if you are reading this and you feel hopeless or like you can’t do it anymore, find it in yourself to push harder I promise you can do it. “The moment you think of giving up, remember the reason you held on for so long.” By far one of my favorite quotes. Love you Demi, what an inspiration ❤️
